
@startuml
skinparam linetype zigzag

class Hospital {
  -id: int
  -name: String
  -allowedExaminationTypes: List<ExaminationType>
}

class ExaminationType {
  -id: int
  -name: String
  -description: String
}

class Doctor {
  -id: int
  -name: String
  -affiliatedHospital: Hospital
}

class Patient {
  -id: int
  -name: String
}

class Problem {
  -id: int
  -name: String
  -description: String
}

class TreatmentPlan {
  -id: int
  -problem: Problem
  -advisedExaminations: List<ExaminationType>
}

class ActualTreatment {
  -id: int
  -patient: Patient
  -doctor: Doctor
  -treatmentPlan: TreatmentPlan
  -examinations: List<Examination>
  -additionalActions: List<String>
}

class Examination {
  -id: int
  -type: ExaminationType
  -hospital: Hospital
  -date: Date
}

class PermissionRequest {
  -id: int
  -hospital: Hospital
  -examinationType: ExaminationType
  -status: String
}

' Associations
Hospital "1" -- "0..*" PermissionRequest : applies for
Hospital "1" -- "0..*" ExaminationType : allows
Doctor "1" -- "0..*" Patient : treats
Doctor "1" -- "0..*" ActualTreatment : creates
Problem "1" -- "1" TreatmentPlan : has
TreatmentPlan "1" -- "0..*" ExaminationType : advises
ActualTreatment "1" -- "0..*" ExaminationType : includes (via examinations)
ActualTreatment "1" -- "0..*" String : additional actions
Examination "1" -- "1" ExaminationType : of type
Examination "1" -- "1" Hospital : performed at
@enduml

---

### 📌 Explanation of Key Elements:

- **`Hospital`**: Has allowed examination types and can apply for permissions.
- **`ExaminationType`**: Represents types like "cardiologic test", "NMR scan", etc.
- **`Doctor`**: Is affiliated with a hospital and may create actual treatments.
- **`Patient`**: Undergoes treatment and may have their exams done at different hospitals.
- **`Problem`**: A condition or issue a patient presents with.
- **`TreatmentPlan`**: Defines advised examinations per problem.
- **`ActualTreatment`**: The real treatment applied, which may differ from the plan.
- **`Examination`**: An instance of an exam, associated with a type and a hospital.
- **`PermissionRequest`**: A request by a hospital to allow a specific exam type.

